@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "MyTiles" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on a tile corresponding to the 'Next Tile'
shown on the right of the game board, that tile will be removed from
the board and a new tile will be shown as the next tile.

  When a tile is removed, it may reveal a tile that was hidden
'under' that tile. the number of tiles stacked at one position is
indicated by its border thickness, the thicker the border, the more
tiles that are stacked one above another, up to five tiles high.

  As you can see, the tiles you have to find are always in a
numerical order (from 0 to 9 and then to 0 and so on...). If you
click on another numbered tile than what is shown on the 'Next tile',
it will be ignored.

@{b}Hint@{ub}: when playing, try to choose the tiles that are the highest
      ones, because they may hide the only next numbered tile
      available at that time.

  If the 'Next tile' isn't visible on the game board, the game is
over and the game restarts.

  When a game board is completed, MyTiles displays a new board and the
game continues. Try to get as many tiles as you can...

  Have fun!

